  "title": "CSP Resident Manager / Head of Corporate Services",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p> • Lead and manage <strong>Corporate Service Provider (CSP) licence application</strong> with ACRA</p><p> • Act as <strong>Resident Manager / Key Person</strong> for CSP regulatory matters</p><p> • Design, implement and maintain <strong>AML / CFT, KYC, client risk assessment frameworks</strong></p><p> • Oversee client onboarding, due diligence and ongoing compliance</p><p> • Handle and respond to <strong>ACRA inspections, regulatory queries and audits</strong></p><p> • Review and approve high-risk / overseas client cases</p><p> • Supervise corporate secretarial and compliance staff</p><p> • Ensure all corporate services activities comply with Singapore regulations<br /></p><p>⸻<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p> • Singapore <strong>Citizen or PR</strong> (strongly preferred)</p><p> • <strong>8+ years</strong> experience in corporate services, CSP, professional firm, or similar</p><p> • <strong>Hands-on experience with CSP licence application and/or ACRA inspection</strong></p><p> • Strong working knowledge of:</p><p> • Companies Act</p><p> • AML / CFT regulations</p><p> • KYC / UBO identification</p><p> • Able to independently draft policies, procedures and regulatory responses</p><p> • <strong>ICSA / CGI qualification</strong> is a strong advantage</p><p> • Comfortable taking regulatory ownership and accountability</p>",
